kipedia.org/wiki/Crash_test" title=3D"Crash test">crash test</a> by the <a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Insurance_Institute_for_Highway_Safet=
y" title=3D"Insurance Institute for Highway Safety">Insurance Institute for=
 Highway Safety</a></figcaption></figure>
<p>Safety is a state that implies being protected from any risk, danger, da=
mage, or cause of injury. In the automotive industry, safety means that use=
rs, operators, or <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Manufacturers" c=
lass=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Manufacturers">manufacturers</a> do not face =
any risk or danger coming from the motor vehicle or its spare parts. Safety=
 for the automobiles themselves implies that there is no risk of damage.
</p><p>Safety in the automotive industry is particularly important and ther=
efore highly regulated. <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Automobile=
s" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Automobiles">Automobiles</a> and other <a=
 href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Motor_vehicles" class=3D"mw-redirect=
" title=3D"Motor vehicles">motor vehicles</a> have to comply with a certain=
 number of regulations, whether local or international, in order to be acce=
pted on the market. The standard <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/I=
SO_26262" title=3D"ISO 26262">ISO 26262</a>, is considered one of the best =
practice frameworks for achieving automotive <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedi=
a.org/wiki/Functional_safety" title=3D"Functional safety">functional safety=
</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-10" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wiki=
pedia.org/wiki/Automotive_industry#cite_note-10"><span class=3D"cite-bracke=
t">[</span>10<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>In case of safety issues, danger, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.or=
g/wiki/Product_defect" title=3D"Product defect">product defect</a>,<sup id=
=3D"cite_ref-11" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Automotive_industry#cite_note-11"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>1=
1<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-12" cla=
ss=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Automotive_indust=
ry#cite_note-12"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>12<span class=3D"cite=
-bracket">]</span></a></sup> or faulty procedure during the manufacturing o=
f the motor vehicle, the maker can request to return either a batch or the =
entire production run. This procedure is called <a href=3D"https://en.wikip=
edia.org/wiki/Product_recall" title=3D"Product recall">product recall</a>. =
Product recalls happen in every industry and can be production-related or s=
tem from raw materials.
</p><p>Product and operation tests and inspections at different stages of t=
he <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Value_chain" title=3D"Value cha=
in">value chain</a> are made to avoid these product recalls by ensuring end=
-user security and safety and compliance with the automotive industry requi=
rements. However, the automotive industry is still particularly concerned a=
bout product recalls, which cause considerable financial consequences.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Economy">Economy</h2><span =
class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a =
