<p>These were the ten largest manufacturers by production volume as of 2017=
,<sup id=3D"cite_ref-oi15_59-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/Automotive_industry#cite_note-oi15-59"><span class=3D"cit=
e-bracket">[</span>59<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> of whi=
ch the eight largest were in the top 8 positions since <a href=3D"https://e=
n.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fiat_Chrysler_Automobiles" title=3D"Fiat Chrysler Auto=
mobiles">Fiat's 2013 acquisition</a> of the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia=
.org/wiki/Chrysler" title=3D"Chrysler">Chrysler</a> Corporation (although t=
he <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/PSA_Group" title=3D"PSA Group">=
PSA Group</a> had been in the top 8 1999 to 2012, and 2007 to 2012 one of t=
he eight largest along with the seven largest as of 2017) and the five larg=
est in the top 5 positions since 2007, according to OICA, which, however, s=
topped publishing statistics of motor vehicle production by manufacturer af=
ter 2017. All ten remained as the ten largest automakers by sales until <a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stellantis" title=3D"Stellantis">the =
merger between Fiat-Chrysler and the PSA Group in early 2021</a>; only <a h=
ref=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Renault" title=3D"Renault">Renault</a>=
 was degraded to 11th place, in 2022, when being surpassed by both <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/BMW" title=3D"BMW">BMW</a> (which became =
the 10th largest in 2021) and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chan=
gan_Automobile" title=3D"Changan Automobile">Chang'an</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_r=
ef-60" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Automot=
ive_industry#cite_note-60"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>60<span cla=
ss=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
